body:
## Summary

This is a minor update to the DC/OS Commons SDK.

### Improvements
- Expose evaluation outcomes as a debug endpoint.  ([#1743](https://github.com/mesosphere/dcos-commons/pull/1743))
- Bump JRE to 1.8u162.  ([#2135](https://github.com/mesosphere/dcos-commons/pull/2135))
- The bootstrap utility now verifies by default that the task's DNS resolves to its IP address (this behavior can be disabled).  ([#2029](https://github.com/mesosphere/dcos-commons/pull/2029))
- A default CLI can now be used rather than building one.  ([#1986](https://github.com/mesosphere/dcos-commons/pull/1986))

### Bug Fixes
- Improvements to the pod pause feature. ([#1989](https://github.com/mesosphere/dcos-commons/pull/1989))
- Improve handling of unexpected task statuses. ([#2087](https://github.com/mesosphere/dcos-commons/pull/2087))

## Upgrade Instructions

### JRE Path

The bundled JRE (1.8u162) no longer has a separately bundled JCE. If you have been using `{{jre-jce-unlimited-url}}` in resource.json, replace it with `{{jre-url}}`.

In the `marathon.json.mustache` file, you will need to update `JAVA_HOME=$(ls -d $MESOS_SANDBOX/jre*/)` to `JAVA_HOME=$(ls -d $MESOS_SANDBOX/jdk*/jre/)` (note, you'll need to make this change anywhere that you've calculated JAVA_HOME in this way).

### Default CLI

You can now consume a "default" CLI if you do not need any customization in your CLI. Simply edit the CLI section of your `resource.json` to read (replacing `<version>` with the correct version):
```
"cli":{
    "binaries":{
      "darwin":{
        "x86-64":{
          "contentHash":[ { "algo":"sha256", "value":"{{sha256:dcos-service-cli-darwin@https://downloads.mesosphere.com/dcos-commons/artifacts/<version>/SHA256SUMS}}" } ],
          "kind":"executable",
          "url":"https://downloads.mesosphere.com/dcos-commons/artifacts/<version>/dcos-service-cli-darwin"
        }
      },
      "linux":{
        "x86-64":{
          "contentHash":[ { "algo":"sha256", "value":"{{sha256:dcos-service-cli-linux@https://downloads.mesosphere.com/dcos-commons/artifacts/<version>/SHA256SUMS}}" } ],
          "kind":"executable",
          "url":"https://downloads.mesosphere.com/dcos-commons/artifacts/<version>/dcos-service-cli-linux"
        }
      },
      "windows":{
        "x86-64":{
          "contentHash":[ { "algo":"sha256", "value":"{{sha256:dcos-service-cli.exe@https://downloads.mesosphere.com/dcos-commons/artifacts/<version>/SHA256SUMS}}" } ],
          "kind":"executable",
          "url":"https://downloads.mesosphere.com/dcos-commons/artifacts/<version>/dcos-service-cli.exe"
        }
      }
    }
```

### build.sh

`build_framework.sh` has been replaced by `build_package.sh`. Replace `build_framework.sh` by adding a call to `${ROOT_DIR}/gradlew -p ${FRAMEWORK_DIR} check distZip` before the existing `build_framework.sh` call, and then replace that call with `build_package.sh`.


Additionally, `--artifact` has been replaced with `-a`.

### `com.mesosphere.sdk.api` ==> `com.mesosphere.sdk.http`

The Java package `com.mesosphere.sdk.api` has been renamed `com.mesosphere.sdk.http`. If used, it will need to be updated.
